                        <condition key="deficient">The sewing is partly missing; almost all quires
                           are unbound. The back board is broken and has been repaired with a thread
                           of plastic and metal wire.
 The Ms. shows traces of intensive
                           use.
 Many leaves are badly stained with wax and dirt (e.g., <locus target="#20v">20v</locus>, 26r, 31r, 51r-v).
 Text is barely
                           legible or illegible on some leaves, e.g., <locus target="#27r">27r</locus>, 54v, 57ra, 75ra.
 The Ms. is damaged by rodents in
                           the bottom margin of fols. 1-10; by fire, e.g., on <locus target="#32">32</locus>, 38, 53, 78, with loss of text.
 Remains of glues are
                           preserved on the inner side of left board.
 <locus target="#131">131</locus> is a leaf of different size originating from another
                           (somewhat older) Ms.
 Tears amended on <locus target="#95">95</locus>, 121.</condition>
