                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#45rb">f. 45rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ወልደ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ወብእሲቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሩፋኤል፡ ውሉዱ፡
                              መንበረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ መኳዕ፡ በሲመቱ፡ ፆተ፡ ሥላሴ።</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in deep brown ink and states that Mänbärä
                              Śǝllāse donated this book to Mikāʾel Bet Mäkʷaʿ during the tenure of
                              Ṣotä Śǝllāse. Her father Walda Ḥawāryāt and her mother Walatta Rufāʾel
                              are also mentioned. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#45rb">f. 45rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝ፡ መጽሀፈ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡ ሙኵዕ፡
                              ዘወሐቦ፡ መንበረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ በሲመቱ፡ ለጾታ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወጻፌ፡ ዝንቱ፡ ገብረ፡ ትወይሕ። …</q>
                           
                           <note> The note is crudely written in dark grey ink and states that
                              Mänbärä Śǝllāse donated this book to Mikāʾel Bet Mukʷǝʿ during the
                              tenure of Ṣotä Śǝllāse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#129va">f. 129va</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ቤት፡
                              መኳዕ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ መንበረ፡ ሥላሴ፡ በሲመተ፡ ፆታ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወምስለ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ደቂቀ፡ ማኅበረ፡ ካህናት፡
                              ወዲያቆናት፡ ኀቡረ፡ ይምህሮሙ፡ ወይሠሃሎሙ፡ መንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። </q>
                           
                           <note> The note is written in deep brown ink, possibly in the same hand
                              as Additio 1. It states that Mänbärä Śǝllāse donated this book to
                              Mikāʾel Bet Mäkʷaʿ during the tenure of Ṣotä Śǝllāse. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">-<desc> Texts I, II, III contain musical notation signs.
 -
                           Tamallas-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines (┴), indicating
                           the place where the omissions, written in the upper margin, belong:
                              <locus target="#8rb">8rb</locus>, 87vb, 126ra, 128ra.
 - Omitted
                           letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#16vb">16vb</locus>, 26rb, 62va, 65ra, 68va.
 - Omitted words added at
                           the end of the line in small script: <locus target="#62va">62va</locus>,
                           124rb.
 - Immediate corrections indicated by series of dashes above
                           and below the letters or the words: <locus target="#13ra">13ra</locus>,
                           22va, 83va, 89ra, 124rb.
 - Corrections indicated by two lines in
                           black ink over the word: <locus target="#10rb">10rb</locus>, 59ra,
                           98va.
 - Lacunae (spaces for names left unfilled) on many leaves:
                           e.g., <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>, 14vb, 30va, 41vb, 59rb,
                           95va.
 - Numbers are written in red ink in the left margin of <locus target="#6va">6va</locus>, 7ra (here also in the intercolumn), 74ra
                           (here also in black ink), 85va (here also in black ink).
 - Pen
                           trial: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1v, 132r.
 - Scribbles: <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>, 9ra, 33va, 69v, 130r.
 - Prayers and
                           other minor texts are crudely written in dark grey ink, possibly in the
                           same hand as Additio 2, on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 2vb (here
                           effaced), 129v, 130r, 130v, 132r, 132v. One of the prayers on <locus target="#129vb">129vb</locus> mentions the date 1903 year of mercy (=
                           1911 AD).
 - A prayer with musical notation signs is written,
                           possibly in the main hand, on <locus target="#2va">2va</locus>.
 -
                              <locus target="#131">131</locus> originates from a Maṣḥafa Täklil
                           “Book of the Marriage Ritual”.
 - Note almost illegible in deep brown
                           ink on <locus target="#55vb">55vb</locus>.</desc></item>
